OL,7,FSome contributors to the record said
OL,8,Fsenior medics made end-of-life
OL,9,Fdecisions for patients, partly to
OL,10,Fspare their junior colleagues having
OL,11,Fto do it.
OL,13,FOne said of young doctors: "They were
OL,14,Fsurrounded by people dying, more than
OL,15,Fone patient in a day, and often
OL,16,Funcomfortable and looking distressed
OL,17,Fwhen they died.
